f Middle English; in addition, the book employs an Evolutionary Game Theory model. The results are approached from an ‘evolutionary construction grammar’ perspective, combining evolutionary thinking with diachronic constructionist notions, and the alternation’s emergence is interpreted as a story of constructional innovation, competition, cooperation and co-evolution. The book not only provides a thorough and detailed analysis of the history of one of the most-discussed syntactic phenomena in English, but by fusing two frameworks and employing two different methodologies also presents a highly innovative approach to a problem of relevance to historical linguistics in general.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aEnglish languagexGrammar, Historical. 0aEnglish languageyMiddle English, 1100-1500. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aConstructional Competition.  aDative Alternation.  aDitransitive.  aEvolutionary Construction Grammar.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2019 Part 1z978311076246408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton Contemporary 2016-2019z978311074297808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2019 Englishz978311061030708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2019z9783110606287oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831106304420 cprintz978311063034340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311063385640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/978311063